<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE LAST WORD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 When Alex Uchitel described himself as a "godfather" who helped fellow 
immigrants by giving them jobs in his appliance-repair service, he surely could 
not have anticipated the headline identifying his business as "L.A.'s Russian 
(Appliance-Repair) Mafia" (Palm Latitudes, Oct. 16).Off to a gulag for your 
editors for carelessly misrepresenting Uchitel and his highly educated 
colleagues in focusing only on the last word of the item and for failing to 
recognize that such "cleverness" could cause the "melting pot" to do a slow 
burn. 
</P>
<P>
 Sharon Scull 
