<TEXT>
<P>
 JAPANESE JIVE: Wacky and Wonderful Products from Japan by Caroline McKeldin 
(Tengu Books/Weatherhill: $9.95; 80 pp., illustrated, paperback original). 
English writing on T-shirts and product labels is considered very trendy in 
Japan, and these often hysterical examples were obviously created by people who 
don't speak the language, e.g. the beverages, "Plain White Water" and "Pocari 
Sweat." Some of the products sound as bizarre as their names, especially the 
"Soup Sand Series": a serving of soup sealed in a fried crumb crust, presented 
on a hamburger bun with lettuce and mayo to resemble a sandwich. What's the 
Japanese word for yeech?  
</P>
