<BYLINE>
<P>
By Walter Price 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 VERDI: "FALSTAFF." Juan Pons, Daniela Dessi, Roberto Frontali, Bernadette 
Manca di Nissa, Maureen O'Flynn, Ramon Vargas, others; forces of La Scala, 
Riccardo Muti, cond.Sony S2K 58 961. Seldom has the admired Muti found a 
vehicle more suitable to his passion for disciplined detail, sense of 
orchestral color and arching expressive expansion. Taken from live 
performances, this riveting achievement is accomplished, moreover, with a cast 
containing not one truly memorable voice. However, Muti allows his singers 
space to bloom lyrically when the music calls for it. As the Fat Knight, Pons 
finds his best role, the conductor coaxing nuances not usually found in the 
baritone's work. O'Flynn and Vargas, as the young lovers, are the most 
noteworthy, but indicative of the overall effect is the stunning result of 
Muti's loving guidance of Frontali's less than first-rate voice in "E sogno?" 
Walter Price 
</P>
