<P>
BRIEFLY: SCHOLARSHIPS: 7 GET KIWANIS AWARDS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Kiwanis Club of Santa Monica has awarded more than $4,500 in scholarships 
to seven Santa Monica College students in need of financial assistance. 
</P>
<P>
 Each student received $650 as part of the annual Kiwanis scholarship program 
for young people involved in community service who have good academic standing 
and specific educational goals. 
</P>
<P>
 The recipients are Michaela Grube, Yvoune Petrie, Rachael Fromanter, Kathleen 
Savacool, Carolann Miller, Kristen Seraphin and John Davidson. 
</P>
</TEXT>
