<P>
 Reservations are now being taken for the fourth annual Seattle Super Saver 
program that includes discounts up to 50% at participating hotels, attractions, 
restaurants and shops from Jan. 1 to March 31, 1995. To take part, travelers 
must stay overnight at one of the 25 participating lodgings and make their 
reservations directly through the hotel or through Seattle Super Saver.Rates 
range from $49 per room per night at the WestCoast Vance (normally $95), to 
$140 at the Alexis Hotel (normally $185). Visitors will receive a discount 
coupon book when they check in. For more information, contact Seattle Super 
Saver, 520 Pike St., Suite 1300, Seattle 98101; tel. (800) 535-7071 or the 
Seattle-King County Convention and Visitors Bureau, tel. (206) 461-5840. Free 
for the Asking 
</P>
<P>
 Mud or massage? Steam or sauna? Should I try a moor peat bath? "How to Spa 
Like a Pro: A Guide for the Uninitiated" from the Peaks at Telluride sets out 
to answer everything you've always wanted to know about going to a spa but were 
afraid to ask, including "Do I have to get naked in front of strangers?" (Only 
if you want to.) To obtain a copy of the 16-page, pocket-sized brochure contact 
Carefree Resorts, (800) 979-2999. This Week's Holidays 
