<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE MATURE TRAVELER: DISCOUNTS TO PLANT YOUR POLES IN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By HANK KOVELL 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 We continue the roundup of discounts for seniors at U.S. ski resorts. 
</P>
<P>
 Michigan: 
</P>
<P>
 * Crystal Mountain Resort, Thompsonville, has a Silver Streak program for 
those over 55. Free ID card valid for half-price lift rates every day, 
cross-country trails, rental equipment and group lessons plus 10% discount on 
midweek lodging and package plans. Call (800) 968-7686. * Shanty Creek Resort, 
Bellaire. It also has a Silver Streak week, Jan. 23-27, for skiers over 55, who 
will receive free lift tickets and cross-country trail passes. Seniors will 
also receive reduced rates in the Shanty Creek Lodge for the same period. For 
information, brochures and reservations, call (800) 678-4111. 
</P>
<P>
 Utah: 
</P>
<P>
 * Robert Redford's Sundance Resort, Sundance. Those over age 65 ski free all 
day (regular all-day rates: $28). Grandchildren under age 12 ski free. For 
information and brochures, call (800) 892-1600. 
</P>
<P>
 Nevada: 
</P>
<P>
 * Heavenly Lake Tahoe, Stateline. Skiers over age 65 get an all-day senior 
lift ticket for $18, a savings of $24. A half-day senior ticket is $12, good 
from 12:30 to 4 p.m. Senior lift tickets are good any day of the season, 
including holidays and weekends. Heavenly is also offering two three-day Super 
Senior/50+ Skier workshops Feb. 3-5 and March 13-17. Workshops include 
breakfast and lunch daily plus lessons, a personal analysis, videotaping and 
group photos. Workshop price is $299. For brochure and information, call (800) 
243-2836.  
</P>
<P>
 North Carolina: 
</P>
<P>
 The Blue Ridge and Great Smoky Mountains provide plenty of ski spots. Here are 
a sampling: 
</P>
<P>
 * Appalachian Ski Mountain, Blowing Rock. Rates vary. The regular price for a 
ticket for two full weekdays is $36, $22 for those over age 60. Weekends or 
holidays (two days), which are regularly $52, are $34 for seniors. Tickets may 
be purchased for up to five days. For brochures and information, call (800) 
322-2373. 
</P>
<P>
 * Cataloochee Ski Area, Maggie Valley. In the Great Smokies. Free ski-lift 
tickets for anyone over age 65 on weekdays or weekends without restrictions 
throughout the season. Regular adult rates are $29. For a brochure or 
information, call (800) 768-0285. 
</P>
