<HEADLINE>
<P>
SINGLE TAXPAYERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 * Whenever one reads about a proposed middle-class tax cut, it invariably is 
about families and/or tax credits for children, be it for child care or 
educational purposes.The single taxpayer is never given consideration although 
that segment of the population carries a heavy tax burden. 
</P>
<P>
 Perhaps it is time for the single taxpayers to organize and mobilize for 
consideration. The senior population has been most successful in having its 
voice heard by legislators. 
</P>
<P>
 It is time for those who govern to realize that those who are unmarried are 
voters also. Remember us when talking about middle-class tax cuts. We need your 
help too. And there will be more election days to come. 
</P>
<P>
 MICHELE A. SMOLLAR 
</P>
<P>
 Los Angeles 
</P>
