<HEADLINE>
<P>
DISTANCE LEARNING MAY PAY DIVIDENDS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 I found your article "A New College Course" (Nov. 8) on expansion of college 
education through distance learning interesting and informative. It is true 
that distance learning is likely to become a factor in education at all levels. 
</P>
<P>
 Unlike business and industry, education has not changed with the development 
of new tools and technologies. One reason for this may well be that education 
has been unchallenged by marketplace forces such as cost, competition and 
quality control. 
</P>
<P>
 Now these factors are present . . . to bring about radical change to the 
education establishment. 
</P>
<P>
 Education may become a new source of revenue for technically sophisticated 
corporations who possess the capital and intellectual resources to challenge 
the monopoly the traditional public and private schools have enjoyed. Now we 
change or others will engage our clientele! 
</P>
<P>
 ROBERT A. LOMBARDI 
</P>
<P>
 Chancellor 
</P>
