<HEADLINE>
<P>
TREE LOSS TRAGIC 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The cutting down of 2,500 trees at a Mission Viejo development is a tragic 
loss that brings to mind several questions. 
</P>
<P>
 Was the developer required, as part of his plan, to plant trees? Did the 
county approve planting eucalyptus trees rather than a more sensible species? 
Will the developer be required to replace the trees? 
</P>
<P>
 Why were they not topped before they rose to such heights? 
</P>
<P>
 Why is there not a law in Orange County, as there is elsewhere in California, 
requiring a permit to cut trees down because they are a beneficial and precious 
environmentally contributive resource? 
</P>
<P>
 ANDY WING 
</P>
<P>
 Laguna Beach 
</P>
</TEXT>
