<HEADLINE>
<P>
IN REPEAT PERFORMANCE, UTAH DEFEATS BYU AGAIN BY THE SAME SCORE, 34-31 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Mike McCoy flipped a swing pass to Charlie Brown, who ran for a 20-yard 
touchdown with 56 seconds remaining, giving Utah a 34-31 victory over Brigham 
Young on Saturday at Salt Lake City. 
</P>
<P>
 Utah defeated BYU by the same score in Provo last year. 
</P>
<P>
 McCoy finished with four touchdowns passes, two of them to Deron Claiborne, 
while connecting on 18 of 29 passes for 247 yards. 
</P>
<P>
 Brown had 107 yards rushing -- his fourth consecutive game of 100 yards or 
more on the ground. 
</P>
<P>
 Utah is 9-2 overall and 6-2 in the Western Athletic Conference. The Cougars 
finished the regular season 9-3 and 6-2. 
</P>
<P>
 The loss ruined a stellar day for BYU quarterback John Walsh, who connected on 
29 of 46 passes for 324 yards and four touchdowns, with one interception. 
</P>
</TEXT>
