<HEADLINE>
<P>
SOUTHWEST ROUNDUP; TEXAS A&M PULLS PLUG ON TCU 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 No. 9 Texas A&M can't go to the Cotton Bowl because of NCAA probation. Texas 
Christian can't go to the Cotton Bowl because of Texas A&M. 
</P>
<P>
 Corey Pullig threw a touchdown pass on a third-and-long play and the Aggies 
came up with two drive-stopping plays in the third quarter in defeating TCU, 
34-17, at College Station, Tex., on Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
 The Aggies 10-0-1 overall and 6-0-1 in the SWC, completed their first unbeaten 
season since 1956. 
</P>
<P>
 TCU's hopes of upsetting the Aggies fell apart in the third quarter, as the 
Horned Frogs (6-4, 3-3) lost to the Aggies for the 22nd consecutive time. 
</P>
<P>
 The Aggies extended their Kyle Field winning streak to 26 games and their home 
unbeaten string to 30. They were tied by Baylor, 20-20, in 1990. The Aggies 
haven't lost at home since 1989. 
</P>
<P>
 The 23 Aggie seniors became the winningest class in SWC history with 42 
victories overall and a 29-0-1 SWC record. SMU tied A&M, 21-21, this season. 
</P>
<P>
 Navy 29, Rice 17 -- The Midshipmen (3-7) ended the Owls' hopes of a bowl bid 
and a winning season, holding Rice (4-6) without a pass completion in the 
second half at Annapolis, Md. 
</P>
<P>
 Jim Kubiak passed for 242 yards as Navy won two games in a row for the first 
time in 13 months. 
</P>
