<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIVISION V FOOTBALL PLAYOFFS; LOARA MAKING THE MOST OF ITS POSTSEASON 
INVITATION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JON CLIFFORD, SPECIAL TO THE TIMES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 First the Loara Saxons weren't invited to the Southern Section playoffs. Then 
they were. 
</P>
<P>
 Now they are in the second round of the Division V playoffs after upsetting 
Canyon, 10-9, Saturday night at Western High School. 
</P>
<P>
 Sophomore quarterback Archie Lappin, who had never taken a varsity snap, 
conducted the Saxons' game-winning drive. 
</P>
<P>
 With the Saxons trailing, 9-6, with 2 minutes 30 seconds remaining, Lappin 
began his fourth drive of the night at the Saxons' 17. He completed six of 
seven passes, including a 40-yard strike to Shane Thompson that put the ball at 
the Comanches' 21. 
</P>
<P>
 Lappin connected with Dalbert Rodriguez on an 18-yard pass that moved the ball 
to the seven. 
</P>
<P>
 After three plays left the Saxons (6-5) at the two, Rob Crabtree kicked an 
18-yard field goal that cleared the crossbar by less that two feet, giving the 
Saxons a 10-9 lead. 
</P>
<P>
 "(Lappin) came through in the clutch," Loara Coach John de Fries said. "He hit 
some big, big passes. We made the decision to go with him at the end of the 
third quarter because we needed someone to give us a spark." 
</P>
<P>
 Starting quarterback junior Jim Kirkland didn't complete a pass in two 
attempts, and was sacked five times. 
</P>
<P>
 The Saxons trailed, 6-0, in the first quarter when Canyon quarterback Adam 
Hoover scored on a five-yard run. The extra-point kick went wide right, leaving 
the Comanches ahead, 6-0. 
</P>
<P>
 But Loara, which plays El Toro this week, answered early in the second quarter 
on a one-yard run by Kerry Peoples, giving the Saxons a 7-6 lead at halftime. 
</P>
<P>
 Canyon (7-4) jumped ahead with 6:06 left to play on Clay Kilbarger's 26-yard 
field goal. 
</P>
</TEXT>
