<HEADLINE>
<P>
CRESCENTA VALLEY CLOSES GAP AGAINST LA SERNA BUT FALLS, 6-5; WATER POLO 
PLAYOFFS: FALCONS PUSH TOP-SEEDED TEAM MORE THAN THEY DID IN REGULAR-SEASON 
MATCH. 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BRYAN RODGERS, SPECIAL TO THE TIMES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Crescenta Valley High's run through the Southern Section Division III water 
polo playoffs came to an abrupt end in the semifinals thanks to a familiar 
opponent. 
</P>
<P>
 La Serna, the top-seeded team, defeated the Falcons, 6-5, on Saturday at 
Caltech. 
</P>
<P>
 But unlike the teams' regular-season match, which La Serna won, 11-6, 
Crescenta Valley posed a more difficult challenge. 
</P>
<P>
 "We played a better ballgame today," Falcon Coach Pete Loporchio said. "I am 
proud of how we battled back." 
</P>
<P>
 La Serna (27-4) held the upper hand most of the match. The Lancers scored two 
quick goals and kept Crescenta Valley on the defensive early. 
</P>
<P>
 However, each time La Serna appeared on the verge of breaking it open, the 
Falcons (24-5) responded. Crescenta Valley scored two goals early in the fourth 
quarter, forcing La Serna to call a timeout. 
</P>
<P>
 Crescenta Valley's Joey Bennett scored on a perfect two-on-one with Eddie Kim, 
closing the gap to 6-5 with 4 1/2 minutes remaining. 
</P>
</TEXT>
