<P>
HANCOCK ROLLS OVER VENTURA, 51-9 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MIKE BRESNAHAN, SPECIAL TO THE TIMES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 On paper, this game looked pretty bad for the Ventura College football team. 
</P>
<P>
 On the field, it was even worse. 
</P>
<P>
 Ventura ended its season Saturday night with a 51-9 loss to Hancock in a 
Western State Conference Northern Division game. 
</P>
<P>
 The score was ugly, and the stats were uglier. 
</P>
<P>
 Ventura had 18 penalties -- including eight for personal fouls and 
unsportsmanlike conduct -- for 175 yards. 
</P>
<P>
 The Pirates gave up 447 yards. 
</P>
<P>
 Hancock's Reggie Etheridge gained 157 yards in 21 carries and scored on runs 
of two, four, 35 and 78 yards. 
</P>
<P>
 Quarterback Mick Sitarski completed 15 of 21 for 170 yards a and a touchdown 
for Hancock (7-3, 6-3 in the conference, 4-1 in the Northern Division), which 
will likely appear in its first bowl game in 33 years. 
</P>
<P>
 Jason Brown completed 13 of 30 passes for 114 yards for Ventura (4-6, 3-5, 
0-5). Brown had two passes intercepted.  
</P>
<P>
 Ventura linebacker David Davis was ejected in the second quarter for throwing 
what the referee called a retaliatory punch. 
</P>
