<P>
BOYS' BASKETBALL 1994-1995 / GARDEN GROVE LEAGUE; LA QUINTA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 1993-94 RECORDS OVERALL: 15-11 LEAGUE: 9-5 
</P>
<P>
 COACH: RECORD AT SCHOOL Jim Perry: 147-141 04,20,05,06,04 RETURNING STARTERS 
YR. HGT. P Jason Gondringer Sr. 6-2 F Greg Greenfield Sr. 6-1 F Fang Li Jr. 
5-10 G Mike McManus Sr. 5-11 F 04,15,05,06,04 TOP RETURNERS YR. HGT. P Todd 
Butt Jr. 6-2 F Mike Daniels Jr. 5-10 G Dino Dukovic Sr. 6-7 C 04,16,05,06,04 
TOP NEWCOMERS YR. HGT. P Kevin Brower Jr. 6-2 F Ronnie Johnson Sr. 5-7 G Jimmy 
Nguyen So. 5-7 G Scott Ogilvie So. 6-4 C Drew White So. 5-10 G OUTLOOK 
</P>
<P>
 Perry is downplaying his team's chances of winning the league championship, 
but the other Garden Grove coaches aren't and are picking La Quinta as the 
favorite. "We're not as big and athletic as Rancho Alamitos or Pacifica or as 
big as Garden Grove," Perry said. "If our kids do anything, they have a great 
work ethic and they believe very deeply in the system." Garden Grove coaches 
like La Quinta because the Aztecs return four starters and have transfers 
Johnson and Brower, Perry's first transfers since 1986. Johnson didn't want to 
play behind Los Alamitos' Ali Ton, one of the county's premier point guards, so 
he took his quickness and his outside shooting to La Quinta. Brower has never 
played varsity basketball, but Perry likes his defensive toughness and his 
unselfishness. The top returning starter is two-year starter and three-year 
letterman Greenfield, who averaged 15 points, three assists and four rebounds 
last season. 
</P>
