<P>
 1993-94 RECORDS OVERALL: 11-15 LEAGUE: 7-7 
</P>
<P>
 COACH: RECORD AT SCHOOL Don Grable: 11-15 04,20,05,06,05 RETURNING STARTERS 
YR. HGT. P Kit Ratanaphoulee Sr. 5-10 G Mark Udell Sr. 6-0 G Chau Vuong Sr. 6-0 
G-F TOP RETURNERS: None 04,17,05,06,04 TOP NEWCOMERS YR. HGT. P Gary Burns Jr. 
5-9 G Geronimo Cortez Sr. 6-1 G John Elsaesser So. 6-6 C Chris Francis Jr. 6-1 
F Mike Higgins Jr. 6-3 F Gary Hoggatt Jr. 6-7 C Hung Lam Jr. 5-8 G Matt 
Stafford Sr. 6-1 x Thuan Tran Jr. 5-6 G Mitch Udell Sr. 6-0 G OUTLOOK 
</P>
<P>
 The Lobos reached the playoffs last year and they could be there again if 
their young inside players improve throughout the season. Los Amigos' trio of 
guards, Udell, Vuong and Ratanaphoulee, are as good as anybody's. Udell (9 
points) is the leading returning scorer, but he needs help from the other two 
guards who both averaged six points last year. But if the guards are forced to 
do all the shooting, Los Amigos could be in trouble in a league that has some 
talented post players. The top newcomer could be Stafford, who didn't play 
basketball last year. "We're hoping his shooting touch is as good as his touch 
around the green," Grable said of his all-league golfer. "We want to prove 
ourselves as the best defensive team in the league." Grable said. 
</P>
