<HEADLINE>
<P>
BASKETBALL 1994-1995: GARDEN GROVE LEAGUE; PACIFICA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 1993-94 RECORDS OVERALL: 30-2 LEAGUE: 14-0 
</P>
<P>
 COACH: Bob Becker RECORD AT SCHOOL: 30-2 04,20,05,06,04 RETURNING STARTERS YR. 
HGT. P Shane Miller Sr. 6-5 C 04,15,05,06,04 TOP RETURNERS YR. HGT. P Jaimi 
Bessho Sr. 5-9 G Wes Kimura Sr. 5-9 G Eric Martinez Sr. 6-1 F 04,17,05,06,05 
TOP NEWCOMERS YR. HGT. P Ryan Carvaro Jr. 6-0 G Ryan Lee Fr. 5-10 G Verdell 
LeVeaux So. 6-0 G-F Brent Lockett Jr. 6-1 F-G Kyle Seasock Jr. 6-1 F OUTLOOK 
</P>
<P>
 Becker predicted his team would win the league title last season and it did, 
easily. It also won the Southern Section and the Southern California Regional 
title. But with only one starter and two of his top 10 players returning, 
Becker is making no such statements this season. In fact, he's picking his team 
third or fourth, based on what it did during the summer. He's also prepared to 
abandon his up-tempo, frenetic style. "Our whole style is going to be more 
deliberate," he said. "We won't stall, but we will be more patient." Becker is 
trying to be patient with Miller (4 point average, 7 rebounds), whom he needs 
to have a big year. "He's been very frustrated," Becker said. "He's used to 
being unguarded while everybody else was on (Chris) Vlasic and (Jon) Surface. 
It was easy for him to score. Now, he's the guy everyone is going after and 
he's finding out the game is a lot tougher than he thought." Becker will also 
need big years from Bessho, who starts at point guard, and Martinez, who saw 
some playing time in the playoffs. 
</P>
<P>
 SCHEDULE 
</P>
