<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE ROUNDUP; EGGLESTON DRIVES CAL POLY POMONA PAST SCC 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Former Cypress High standout Jessica Eggleston scored 19 points and had 14 
rebounds to lead Cal Poly Pomona to an 84-51 victory over Southern California 
College in the championship game of the Cal Poly Pomona Tournament on Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
 Tina Southard led SCC (1-1) with 14 points.Heather Brannan added 11 and four 
rebounds. 
</P>
<P>
 Michelle Kerzie added 16 points and seven rebounds for Cal Poly Pomona (2-0). 
</P>
<P>
 In Mountain Pacific Sports Federation water polo: 
</P>
<P>
 UC Irvine 11, UC Santa Barbara 10 -- Ofer Horn, a transfer from Santa Barbara, 
scored the winning goal in the closing seconds for visiting Irvine. Mat Maunz 
scored four goals to lead the Anteaters, and Tom Davis had 12 saves. 
</P>
<P>
 Pepperdine 8, Long Beach State 7 -- Greg Finley and Joe Mihalow scored two 
goals each for visiting Long Beach State (5-19). Pepperdine is 15-8. 
</P>
<P>
 In Big West Conference volleyball: 
</P>
<P>
 Nevada 3, Cal State Fullerton 0 -- Tiffany Neumeier had 14 kills for visiting 
Nevada (11-22, 5-13), which won, 15-10, 15-13, 15-9, in the season finale for 
both teams. Jennifer Lipski had 14 kills for the Titans, who finish 1-28, 1-17. 
</P>
<P>
 In a consolation game at The Master's College Tip Off Tournament: 
</P>
<P>
 Southern California College 66, San Jose Christian College 65 -- Brian Carlson 
had 15 and Dan Hyde had 12 to lead Southern California College (1-1). 
</P>
<P>
 Imani Groce had 18 points for San Jose Christian College (0-2). 
</P>
<P>
 In exhibition women's basketball: 
</P>
<P>
 UC Irvine 75, Estonia 72 -- Allah-mi Basheer scored 20 points as host UC 
Irvine defeated Estonia. Basheer also finished with 11 rebounds. 
</P>
</TEXT>
