<HEADLINE>
<P>
LA MIRADA IN PLAYOFFS DESPITE VIOLATION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 La Mirada, which defeated University in the first round of the Division VIII 
football playoffs Friday, will be allowed to continue in the playoffs despite 
using an ineligible player in the regular season, Southern Section officials 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 Suburban League principals met Saturday morning and decided La Mirada would 
remain.The Southern Section did not learn of the matter until late Friday 
afternoon, and principals were unable to convene before the game. La Mirada is 
top-seeded in Division VIII. 
</P>
<P>
 "Personally, I don't think they should be allowed in the playoffs because 
other teams that committed those same infractions aren't," University Coach 
Mark Cunningham said. "After the fact, they realized there was a wrong, and to 
not correct it is wrong from the standpoint of what message are we sending the 
kids? I'm not saying this from the standpoint that University should go on, I'm 
saying they shouldn't be seeded No. 1." 
</P>
<P>
 La Mirada is scheduled to play Duarte in the second round on Friday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
