<HEADLINE>
<P>
RUBBISH-DUMPERS ARE TRASHING THE SYSTEM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Come on, homeowners in the west San Fernando Valley: Why are you still dumping 
refuse unrelated to the earthquake at your curbside with quake materials for 
free pickup by the city? 
</P>
<P>
 The Times recently ran an article stating Los Angeles had thus far spent $61 
million for earthquake removal and dumping and its services are expected to 
continue till Jan. 17, the anniversary of the quake.Would you hazard a guess on 
these final costs, ultimately born by the taxpayer? 
</P>
<P>
 As I ride my bike in the Chatsworth area, I see supposed quake-damage 
materials at the curb which include garage refuse, Christmas boxes and tree 
branches. What do these have to do with the quake?  
</P>
<P>
 Contractors should have been responsible for all debris resulting from their 
reconstruction. 
</P>
<P>
 It is time for Valleyites to exhibit some pride and responsibility in their 
towns. 
</P>
<P>
 MARILYN WARD FLOYD 
</P>
<P>
 Chatsworth 
</P>
</TEXT>
