</P>
<P>
 1994: 8.1% 
</P>
<P>
 Source: Bloomberg Business News Worst Bear Markets 
</P>
<P>
 Because a bond pays a fixed yield, rising yields on newly issued bonds 
automatically devalue older bonds, pushing their prices down. Over the past 
year, prices have fallen so far that bondholders' total return -- interest 
payments less price decline -- has been negative. 
</P>
