COMMUNITY NEWS: SOUTH: SOUTH-CENTRAL; REDEVELOPMENT IS TOPIC OF MEETING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A community meeting to outline a recommendation to establish a redevelopment 
project in a riot- and earthquake-damaged area of South-Central will be held 
Dec. 6 at the Hubert Humphrey Health Center. 
</P>
<P>
 Residents, property owners, business people and community leaders are asked to 
attend the 5:45 p.m. meeting in the center's auditorium at 5850 Main St. The 
meeting is hosted by the City Council District 9 Community Advisory Committee. 
Councilwoman Rita Walters and members of her staff are scheduled to attend. 
</P>
<P>
 The redevelopment project would target a 5,600-acre area bounded by the Santa 
Monica (10) Freeway, 84th Street, Alameda Street and Vermont Avenue. It would 
aim to revitalize commercial and industrial areas. 
</P>
<P>
 Information: (213) 977-1640. 
