<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS: SOUTHWEST: DAY CENTER OPEN FOR ALZHEIMER'S PATIENTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 People Coordinated Services, a nonprofit community service agency, has opened 
a new center that offers day care for adults suffering from Alzheimer's 
disease. 
</P>
<P>
 The Alzheimer's Adult Day Care and Resource Center at 4703 S. Crenshaw Blvd. 
offers a range of services that include care-giver and family education and 
training; social activities; arts and crafts; independent living skills; 
self-esteem building and grooming skills development, and lunch and 
snacks.Charges for all services are based on a sliding scale. 
</P>
<P>
 Center officials said that the aim of the Alzheimer's program is to encourage 
the individuals to socialize and to remain as independent as possible, as well 
as to provide care-givers with education, support and relief from the demands 
of round-the-clock care. 
</P>
<P>
 The center is open Monday through Friday, 8:30 a.m. to 5 p.m. Information: 
(213) 295-9925. 
</P>
