</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 In a continuing effort to fight breast and cervical cancer, the Northeast 
Community Clinic offers free health screenings for low-income and uninsured 
women. 
</P>
<P>
 For four years, the clinic has provided free Pap smears, which are used to 
detect cervical cancer, and breast examinations, citing studies that show that 
older and low-income women do not regularly receive such exams, spokesman Eddie 
Farias said. 
</P>
<P>
 The clinic is at 5809 N. Figueroa St. Appointments are required. 
