 Rep. Sam Gejdenson (D-Conn.) and Republican challenger Edward W. Munster filed 
separate motions Friday, each maintaining that he had lost votes in a recount, 
which left Gejdenson ahead by four votes out of nearly 160,000 cast in the 2nd 
District. The high court has until Dec. 19 to rule. 
