Lawndale on Friday. 
</P>
<P>
 Carlos Figueroa was booked by sheriff's deputies after the death of Esmeralda 
Figueroa, who was struck by his car, which had been left idling and unattended 
in a driveway. 
</P>
<P>
 Deputies said Carlos Figueroa had left the car with its engine running while 
he went inside the house. A 2-year-old child climbed behind the steering wheel 
and threw the vehicle into gear. It struck Esmeralda and her 4-year-old sister, 
Dora, who had been playing nearby. 
</P>
<P>
 Dora was treated at a hospital and released. Esmeralda was hospitalized and 
died Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
 Carlos Figueroa was being held on $25,000 bond at the Lennox station and is to 
be arraigned Tuesday in South Bay Municipal Court. 
