<HEADLINE>
<P>
BOMB INJURES OFFICER'S FATHER; 2 YOUTHS HELD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Two juveniles were arrested Saturday and charged as adults in connection with 
a bombing that critically injured the father of a police officer. 
</P>
<P>
 Frank Busnuk, 73, father of Capt. Gerard F. Busnuk, was in critical condition 
at the Maryland Shock Trauma Center after a package placed on top of his son's 
car exploded, officials said. 
</P>
